Class TestStepProcessor

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.jayway.android.robotium.remotecontrol.client.processor.AbstractProcessor
      • org.safs.android.engine.processor.SAFSProcessor
        • org.safs.android.engine.processor.TestStepProcessor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ProcessorInterface
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    CheckBoxProcessor, ComboBoxProcessor, DataPickerProcessor, EditTextProcessor, GridViewProcessor, ListViewProcessor, ProgressBarProcessor, RoutingViewProcessor, ScrollBarProcessor, TabControlProcessor, TextViewProcessor, TimePickerProcessor, ViewProcessor

    public abstract class TestStepProcessor
extends SAFSProcessor
    Abstract class used to process ComponentFunctions in the remote (on-device) SAFSTestRunner.

    Each concrete subclass will extend this class and implement the required processComponentFunction method.

    The SAFSTestRunner should expect to execute from Properties with the following settings:

      SAFSMessage.KEY_TARGET=SAFSMessage.target_safs_<cf_processor>
      SAFSMessage.KEY_WINNAME=<window name>
      SAFSMessage.KEY_WINREC=<window recognition string>
      SAFSMessage.KEY_COMPNAME=<child component name>
      SAFSMessage.KEY_COMPREC=<child component recognition string>
      SAFSMessage.KEY_COMMAND=<cf_action>
      SAFSMessage.PARAM_TIMEOUT=<seconds>

    Upon a valid and complete execution the SAFSTestRunner is expected to return:

      SAFSMessage.KEY_ISREMOTERESULT=true
      SAFSMessage.KEY_REMOTERESULTCODE=int
      SAFSMessage.KEY_REMOTERESULTINFO=String

    Any command returning a REMOTERESULTINFO should format it in the exact manner documented in the SAFS Keyword Reference for that command. This processor will simply forward that info into the testRecordData used by the engine using this processor.

    As specific commands require additional parameters they are sent as:

      SAFSMessage.PARAM_1=val
      SAFSMessage.PARAM_2=val
      etc...
      SAFSMessage.PARAM_9=val

      • processProperties

        public void processProperties(java.util.Properties props)
        Implements Component Function handling initialization by first finding the necessary Window and Component objects before routing the call to processComponentFunction(). The routine will issue appropriate errors if the Window or Component names are missing, or if the recognition strings for the objects are missing. It call retrieveParameters(Properties) to initialize SAFSProcessor.params
        Specified by:
        processProperties in interface ProcessorInterface
        Overrides:
        processProperties in class AbstractProcessor
        See Also:
        ProcessorInterface.processProperties(Properties)

      • convertCoords

        public java.lang.String[] convertCoords(java.lang.String coords)
        Convert coordinates string of the formats:
        • "x;y"
        • "x,y"
        • "x y"
        • "Coords=x;y"
        • "Coords=x,y"
        • "Coords=x y"
        into a java.awt.Point object.

        Subclasses may override to convert alternative values, such as Row and Col values as is done in org.safs.rational.CFTable

        Parameters:
        coords, - String x;y or x,y or Coords=x;y or Coords=x,y
        Returns:
        String[]{x,y}, or String[0]{} if invalid
